@page "/about"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>About — NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="NavTour is built by P4 Software, part of Grupo Barrdega — serving 5,000+ business clients with proven multi-tenant SaaS infrastructure." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="mkt-section">
    <div class="mkt-container" style="max-width:680px">
        <h1 class="text-center">About NavTour</h1>
        <p class="text-center" style="margin-top:var(--space-5);font-size:var(--text-xl)">We believe every B2B company should be able to show their product — not just talk about it.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="mkt-section-alt">
    <div class="mkt-container" style="max-width:680px">
        <div class="reveal">
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-4)">Interactive demos shouldn't be a luxury. Leading platforms charge $500–$1,000+ per month with rigid annual contracts, putting them out of reach for most teams. NavTour makes interactive product demos accessible to every B2B company — starting free, with Pro plans at $99/month.</p>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-3)">We're building the demo platform we always wanted: powerful enough for enterprise sales teams, simple enough for a solo founder, and priced so that budget is never the reason a team can't show their product.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:var(--space-16)">
            <h2>Built on Proven Infrastructure</h2>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-4)">NavTour is built by P4 Software, the technology division of Grupo Barrdega. Our multi-tenant SaaS platform already serves 5,000+ business clients across Latin America and the United States. NavTour runs on the same battle-tested infrastructure — the same security standards, the same reliability, the same compliance posture.</p>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-3)">This isn't a startup guessing at scale. It's a proven platform team building a new product on top of infrastructure that already handles enterprise workloads daily.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:var(--space-16)">
            <h2>Why We Built This</h2>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-4)">We saw our own sales teams struggle with the same problem every B2B company faces: prospects want to experience the product before buying, but live demos are expensive and don't scale. The existing solutions were either too expensive or too complex for most teams.</p>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-3)">So we built NavTour — first for ourselves, now for everyone. We started with the premise that a demo platform should be free to try, affordable to scale, and powerful enough to handle enterprise requirements. That mission hasn't changed.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* Timeline *@
<section class="mkt-section">
    <div class="mkt-container" style="max-width:680px">
        <div class="mkt-section-heading reveal">
            <h2>Our Journey</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mkt-timeline reveal">
            <div class="mkt-timeline-item">
                <div class="mkt-timeline-year">2024</div>
                <h3>The Problem</h3>
                <p>P4 Software's sales team identifies the need for interactive demos. Existing solutions are too expensive at $500+/mo with annual contracts.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mkt-timeline-item">
                <div class="mkt-timeline-year">Early 2025</div>
                <h3>Internal Prototype</h3>
                <p>Engineering team builds first version of Chrome extension capture and demo player. Used internally by P4's sales team for 6 months.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mkt-timeline-item">
                <div class="mkt-timeline-year">Late 2025</div>
                <h3>Product Development</h3>
                <p>Full product buildout: annotations engine, personalization tokens, analytics dashboard, lead capture, and REST API. Architecture validated at scale on P4 infrastructure.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mkt-timeline-item">
                <div class="mkt-timeline-year">2026</div>
                <h3>Public Launch</h3>
                <p>NavTour launches publicly with free Starter plan. Mission: make interactive demos accessible to every B2B company, not just those with enterprise budgets.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* Values *@
<section class="mkt-section-alt">
    <div class="mkt-container">
        <div class="mkt-section-heading reveal">
            <h2>What We Stand For</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mkt-grid mkt-grid-4 reveal-stagger">
            <div class="mkt-value-card">
                <h3>Accessible by Default</h3>
                <p>Pricing should never be the reason a team can't show their product. Free tier forever, transparent pricing, no annual lock-in.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mkt-value-card">
                <h3>API-First</h3>
                <p>Every feature is accessible via API. We build for developers and operators who want to automate, integrate, and extend.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mkt-value-card">
                <h3>Privacy-Aware</h3>
                <p>Your data is yours. SOC 2 compliant, GDPR ready, no third-party data sharing. Enterprise customers can self-host for full control.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mkt-value-card">
                <h3>Builder-Friendly</h3>
                <p>We build tools for builders. Clean UI, fast workflows, no unnecessary complexity. If a feature doesn't help you build better demos, we don't ship it.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* Team *@
<section class="mkt-section">
    <div class="mkt-container" style="max-width:680px">
        <div class="reveal">
            <h2>The Team</h2>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-4)">NavTour is built by a cross-functional team of engineers, designers, and go-to-market professionals within P4 Software. We combine deep SaaS infrastructure expertise with frontline sales experience — because we're building the tool we use ourselves every day.</p>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-3)">Our team is distributed across Latin America and the United States, bringing diverse perspectives to a product built for global go-to-market teams. We ship fast, listen to customers, and iterate based on real usage data.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* Metrics *@
<section class="mkt-section-alt">
    <div class="mkt-container text-center reveal">
        <div class="mkt-metrics">
            <div>
                <div class="mkt-metric-value">5,000+</div>
                <p class="mkt-metric-label">Clients served by P4 Software</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="mkt-metric-value">99.9%</div>
                <p class="mkt-metric-label">Uptime SLA</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="mkt-metric-value">2 countries</div>
                <p class="mkt-metric-label">LATAM + US</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* Careers *@
<section class="mkt-section">
    <div class="mkt-container text-center" style="max-width:560px">
        <div class="reveal">
            <h2>Join Us</h2>
            <p style="margin-top:var(--space-4)">We're always looking for talented people who want to build tools that make B2B selling more human. If you're passionate about great product experiences, we'd love to hear from you.</p>
            <a href="/contact" class="mkt-btn mkt-btn-secondary" style="margin-top:var(--space-6)">Get in Touch</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<CtaSection Title="Join us" Subtitle="Start building interactive demos today." />
